Senior Platform & Infrastructure Engineer (Kafka 3.4.x, Spark 3.5.x, dbt 0.22.x) – 7+ years of enterprise data pipeline design and deployment, with deep experience in Confluent Platform (Kafka Streams, KSQL), Spark Structured Streaming, and dbt ELT (core + integrations), as well as familiarity with dbt profiler and dbt Docs. Must be proficient in Python 3.10+ (asyncio, pandas) and Go 1.20+ for custom connector development, and have solid Linux (RHEL/CentOS 8+ / Ubuntu 22.04) administration skills, Docker 20.x, Kubernetes 1.27+ (EKS / GKE). Strong background in schema registry management, Avro/Protobuf serialization, and Kafka security (SSL, SASL‑SCRAM, RBAC). Experience designing and troubleshooting multi‑cluster Kafka deployments (100+ brokers) and Spark clusters (1,000+ worker nodes) in a hybrid cloud (AWS/GCP) environment is required. 

Qualifications: 
• 5+ years in data engineering or platform engineering role, with 3+ years specifically on Kafka, Spark, and dbt; 
• Proficiency in Terraform 1.5+ and Helm 3.x for IaC; 
• Experience with Airflow 2.6+, dbt docs generation, and dbt Cloud or local deployment; 
• Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions or GitLab CI) that integrate dbt tests, schema validations, and Spark job orchestration.

Preferred: 
• Confluent Certified Developer or Administrator certification; 
• Certified Kafka Expert or Confluent Professional Learning (K3E); 
• GCP Certified Data Engineer or AWS Certified Big Data – Specialty. 

Location: New York City office (hybrid, 2 days onsite) or fully remote for US–time‑zone candidates. Full‑time, C2C not accepted. Must be available to start within 4–6 weeks.
